      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% on the fine mesh used for production runs.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed across three mesh refinement levels (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.4M cells). GCI on relative hemolysis index: 3.1% coarse-to-medium, 1.4% medium-to-fine. Production runs use 14.4M cell mesh. y+ < 1 maintained at all blade surfaces."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must match COU operating envelope: flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, blood analog fluid at 37°C.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro validation experiments conducted at 2, 4, and 6 L/min flow rates and 2500, 3000, 3500 RPM. Temperature controlled at 37 ± 0.5°C using glycerol-water blood analog (viscosity 3.5 cP). Conditions fully span the COU operating envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
