      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly linked to the clinical risk metric and computable from CFD outputs without unvalidated post-processing transforms.",
      "rationale": "RH index is computed directly from CFD-predicted shear stress and exposure time using the validated Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. This QoI maps directly to the device submission acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate). No intermediate unvalidated transforms required."
    },
