      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published performance for rotating blood pump flows (Fraser et al., 2011; Hariharan et al., 2011). Formal model-form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties must be traceable to measurements or published standards; sensitivity analysis performed for key uncertain inputs.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles derived from ultrasonic flow meter measurements (±1.5% accuracy). Blood analog viscosity measured at 37°C per ISO 3105. Rotational speed set from tachometer readings (±5 RPM). Sensitivity analysis performed for inlet turbulence intensity (range 1–10%): RH index varies by less than 2.1%. The primary hemolysis boundary condition dataset (PIV inlet profiles, material properties, and operating point specifications) was assembled during model development and carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-22T00:00:00Z. A subsequent model revision on 2025-11-14T00:00:00Z updated the impeller blade geometry tolerance representation to reflect revised manufacturing drawings; the project team determined this geometric update was not material to the inlet boundary condition or fluid property datasets and therefore did not re-acquire experimental input data. This assessment proceeds on the basis that the pre-revision dataset remains applicable, though no formal re-validation study was conducted to confirm equivalence under the revised geometry."
    },
